# =============================================================================
# TADAWUL FAST BRIDGE -- ENTERPRISE GITIGNORE (v7.0.2)
# =============================================================================
#
# QUANTUM EDITION | ZERO-TRUST SECURITY | CLOUD-NATIVE | NARROW-IGNORE POLICY
#
# Core Principles:
# - Track templates, never secrets
# - Prefer narrow (root-anchored) ignores over broad (recursive) ignores
# - Keep source and schema files tracked
# - Ignore generated outputs, runtime state, credentials, and local-only artifacts
#
# v7.0.2 Changes (vs v7.0.1)
# --------------------------
# - FIX HIGH: `tmp/` changed to `/tmp/` (root-only). v7.0.1 ignored ANY
#     `tmp/` directory at ANY depth, including legitimate subproject
#     directories like `scripts/tmp/`, `tests/tmp/`, `src/tmp/`.
# - FIX HIGH: `.env.local.example` added to the negation allow-list.
#     v7.0.1 comment mentioned it as protected, but the actual rule
#     ignored it via the `.env.*` pattern without a re-include. Same
#     for `.env.sample.local`.
# - FIX MEDIUM: `performance_report_*.csv` and siblings root-anchored.
#     v7.0.1 matched these anywhere (so a legitimate sample report in
#     `scripts/` or `docs/examples/` would be dropped). v7.0.2 anchors
#     them to the root so only CI-generated reports at the top level
#     are ignored; curated example reports stay tracked.
# - ADD: `/outputs/` and `/mnt/user-data/outputs/` patterns. These
#     match the dev-tool convention used by Claude/agent tooling so
#     agent-generated artifacts aren't accidentally committed.
# - ADD: Archive formats (`*.zip`, `*.tar.gz`, `*.7z`, `*.tgz`, `*.tar.xz`)
#     commonly generated during deploy/release. Curated
#     archives under `samples/` and `examples/` remain allowed via
#     existing negations.
# - ADD: `node_modules/` and `package-lock.json`-adjacent files for
#     projects that add Node tooling (eslint, prettier, or the Google
#     Apps Script CLI `@google/clasp`).
# - ADD: Root-anchored `/tfb_background_jobs_dead*` / `/tfb_dlq_*` for
#     local DLQ dumps (workers may write these when TFB_WORKER_DLQ_LOCAL=1).
# - ADD: Explicit `.env.production`, `.env.staging`, `.env.dev` notes so
#     the negation allow-list is clearly documented as the only path for
#     tracking env templates.
# - ADD: `*.bak`, `*.backup`, `*.orig`, `*.rej` generic backup patterns
#     so editor backups don't get committed accidentally.
# - ADD: `.claude/` directory (Claude Code session state) -- matches
#     the .cursor/ exclusion pattern.
# - PRESERVED: All v7.0.1 behavior for source files, TFB-specific logs,
#     credentials, Python artifacts, ML artifacts, IDE files, notebooks,
#     and the final "DO NOT IGNORE SOURCE" allowlist.
#
# Version: 7.0.2
# =============================================================================


